Rating: 4
Love this. I used 8 oz of noodles (about 2/3's of a 12-oz bag of noodles), 1/2 cup light sour cream, 1 (12 oz) container low-fat, large curd, cottage cheese, 1 chopped onion sauteed with dash of olive oil, 3 eggs, 1/2 tsp salt, 1/4 tsp pepper, 3-4 tbsp butter. Baked in square, glass casserole sprayed with pam. Note: for 12 oz bag of noodles, use 3/4 cup sour cream (or slightly more), 16 oz cont. cottage cheese, 5 eggs, 3/4 tsp salt, 1/2 tsp pepper (or to taste),1 onion sauteed in olive oil, 4-5 tbsp butter. Add dash of paprika. Bake in rectangular, glass pyrex baking dish (13X9). Delish- serve with sour cream, seasoned salt and pepper. Close your eyes and think PIEROGIS! :) edit this note :

