Rating: 3
Very good basic recipe. I served it as a side dish with roast duck. I made it the night before dinner and actually ate some cold. It is as good cold as it is hot. Next time I may try adding spinach and garlic. A good basic like this lends itself well to variation. Also, I used regualr cottage, regular butter, and regular sour cream..... not all that fat-free crap!

Rating: 3
After trying 3 different recipes, I finally found the one that's perfect. It's simple - I put the noodles into a big aluminum pan, tossed in all the other ingredients, stirred it up and baked. I doubled the recipe for a party so I took it out of the oven, and took it to the party. Great as left over, even cold. Forgot to write that I added sugar instead of salt.

